1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,400
Did you know lightning creates nitrogen?

2
00:00:02,400 --> 00:00:06,800
When lightning strikes, it generates extreme heat, breaking nitrogen molecules apart.

3
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:10,800
This process forms nitrogen oxides, which then mix with rainwater.

4
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:13,600
Plants absorb this nitrogen, essential for growth.

5
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:16,000
So, lightning helps feed the Earth!

6
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:18,800
Yet, climate change is affecting lightning frequency.

7
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:22,000
Less lightning could mean less nitrogen for crops.

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:24,000
